txt.en: 'Well, [placeholder], since we have done what damage we can here, it's about time you meet back up with your friend Dagoras.\n\n'He said he would be headed towards the gates of Isengard and could probably use a hand there.'

'[placeholder]... so you have made it this far? It is good to see you well, for this vale is treacherous, indeed.

'I have yet to find a way into Isengard unseen, but I have spotted someone unusual headed towards Isengard by the road.

'We will want to watch carefully to see what transpires.'
'You should go find your friend Dagoras.'
At Ondor's behest, you wrought havoc among the Warg-riders of the White Hand, putting an end to one threat in Nan Curun√≠r.
Talk to Dagoras at his camp near Isengard
Dagoras mentioned that he was heading north towards the gates of Isengard.\n\nOndor suggested you rejoin Dagoras.
